>Former Norwegian Prime Minister Thorbjrn Jagland was charged with \"gross corruption\" earlier this month over his ties with Epstein, police said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','World Economic Forum boss quits after review of Epstein links','','inherit','closed','closed','','8-revision-v1','','','2026-02-27 10:05:53','2026-02-27 10:05:53','',8,'https://news.loc/?p=9',0,'revision','',0),(10,1,'2026-02-27 10:06:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2026-02-27 10:06:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'https://news.loc/?p=10',0,'post','',0),(11,1,'2026-02-27 10:24:02','2026-02-27 10:24:02','<!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/cpsprodpb/3569/live/0bbe0ec0-135c-11f1-911e-799f6530902b.jpg.webp\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Burger King is testing artificial intelligence-powered employee headsets that monitor staff interactions with customers and oversee store operations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Burger King is testing artificial intelligence-powered employee headsets that monitor staff interactions with customers and oversee store operations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The AI system, called BK Assistant, compiles \"friendliness scores\" at the fast-food chain\'s locations based on employees\' conversations, according to a promotional video the company shared with the BBC.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The chain is currently piloting the system at 500 US restaurants, a spokesperson for Burger King said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The company says the technology is not designed to \"record conversations or evaluate individual employees\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An AI chat-bot dubbed \"Patty\", embedded in the headsets, answers questions from employees about how to prepare menu items and flags when a product needs restocking. But its ability to monitor restaurant staff tees up a debate about surveillance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Burger King\'s chief digital officer told online publication&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.theverge.com/ai-artificial-intelligence/884911/burger-king-ai-assistant-patty\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">The Verge</a>&nbsp;that the fast-food outlet had trained the OpenAI-powered system to identify terms including \"please\" and \"thank you\" in order to evaluate staff friendliness.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The system analyses audio from drive-thru interactions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All US Burger King restaurants are poised to have access to the BK Assistant AI platform by the end of 2026, a company spokesperson told the BBC.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The tool is \"designed to streamline restaurant operations\" to let managers and staff \"focus more on guest service and team leadership\", Restaurant Brands International, the chain\'s parents company, said in a statement on Thursday.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One promotional video for the new AI assistant features the \"Patty\" chat-bot notifying an employee that a machine is running low on Diet Coke. Another worker asks \"Patty\" for a recipe reminder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But the video also highlights an element of the tool that has started to generate backlash online: its ability to closely monitor employee behaviour.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"The team\'s friendliness scores this morning were the highest this week,\" the chat-bot tells a staff member through her headset.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Burger King said that it had explored \"using aggregated keywords, such as common hospitality phrases\" to understand the overall service being offered and to \"recognise teams who deliver great hospitality\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"We believe hospitality is fundamentally human. The role of this technology is to support our teams so they can stay present with guests,\" the firm said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Customer service calls have routinely been recorded and monitored for years. Employees are often aware that they can be assessed to ensure they\'re using the correct language.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But this latest step by Burger King elicited swift condemnation among some social media users who described it as \"dystopian\". Others questioned how accurate the chat-bot headsets will be, given that AI tools have proven to be prone to errors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other fast-food chains have also started to explore the use of AI in its stores. Yum Brands, whose chains include Taco Bell and Pizza Hut, last year announced a partnership with the chip giant Nvidia to develop AI tools for its restaurants.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->','Burger King rolls out AI headsets that track employee \'friendliness\'','','publish','closed','closed','','burger-king-rolls-out-ai-headsets-that-track-employee-friendliness','','','2026-02-27 10:55:30','2026-02-27 10:55:30','',0,'https://news.loc/?p=11',0,'post','',0),(12,1,'2026-02-27 10:24:02','2026-02-27 10:24:02','<!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/cpsprodpb/3569/live/0bbe0ec0-135c-11f1-911e-799f6530902b.jpg.webp\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-blo